					<xs:complexType>
						<xs:sequence>
							<xs:element name="action">
								<xs:annotation>
                                    <xs:documentation>
									Specifies which type of action to take when an attack is detected by HINT.
									When an attack is detected, ShapeShifter can take one of these actions: pass, drop,
									redirect, challenge, default, and custom.

									- Default: default
								</xs:documentation>
                                </xs:annotation>
								<xs:simpleType>
									<xs:restriction base="xs:token">
										<xs:enumeration value="drop">
											<xs:annotation>
                                                <xs:documentation>Stop processing the request.</xs:documentation>
                                            </xs:annotation>
										</xs:enumeration>
										<xs:enumeration value="pass">
